President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 24, 2011, as National Hunting and Fishing Day in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of the outdoors and the responsibility to protect it. It recognizes the long-standing traditions of hunting and fishing in America and the unique connections that hunters and anglers have with the land. The proclamation also highlights the importance of conserving and sustaining the environment, mentioning the America's Great Outdoors Initiative and the Federal Interagency Council on Outdoor Recreation. President Obama calls upon all Americans to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities.